node.text:
Meet Jason and Spencer of @2dads_and_a_benjamin. Two dads and a Benjamin make for one loving family. Listen as they share their love story and their journey of fatherhood.

"On May 15th, 2018, we became parents to Benjamin. And these three years have been wonderful and exhausting and a joy ride and terrifying. A roller coaster joy ride, a roller coaster of emotions."

Tune in to hear their full story and head to our stories to learn what pride means to them.

node.text:
Hello, optimism. 💙 #bye2020 #happynewyear 

CC: 
Goodbye 2020.
It seems you tried your hardest to break our spirit.
Here’s the thing though…you forgot who you were dealing with.
And as hard as you hit us, there was something stronger than you.
Much stronger in fact. 
 
Noah, Imani, Sophia, Liam, Charlotte, Arjun, Mia, Elijah, Lucas, Isabella, Oliver, Mateo…
Hello 2021. Meet Optimism. 
2020 gave us 3,700,203 reasons to believe that we can make this year better than the last. 
 
Carter’s. With you in 2021. With you from the start.

node.text:
To the babies and parents of 2020:

This video was inspired by YOU, all the families who have welcomed new additions this year, featuring babies and parents from across our Carter’s community. It’s a celebration of all that new parenthood brings: hope, joy and, above all, the promise of a better tomorrow.

2020, meet optimism.

Love, Your Carter’s Family

#babiesof2020 #meetoptimism #lovecarters

CC:
Hello, 2020.
We all know you well by now.
It seems you’re on a mission to break our spirit.
Here’s the thing, though…
You forgot who you’re dealing with.
And as hard as you hit us, there’s something stronger than you.
Much stronger, in fact.
Noah, Imani, Sophia, Liam, Charlotte, Arjun, Mia, Elijah, Lucas…
Hello, 2020. Meet optimism.
 
2020 has given us 3,110,758 reasons to believe that we will make tomorrow better than today.
 
Carter’s. With you in 2020. With you from the start.

node.text:
A video from our family to yours. 💙

You're now not only a parent, but a teacher. You're a master chef whipping up treats and the head coach making up plays for their next big backyard game. You may be a brand new mom or dad. You've become your kid's hero whether it's fixing a boo-boo or taking care of someone who needs it most. You're doing great! 
To help families impacted by COVID-19, Carter's is donating $1 million in clothing through our longstanding partnership with Delivering Good. 
We're here for you even when we're apart. 
#makenewmemories #singalong #safeathome #stayhome @oshkoshkids @skiphop #lovecarters #cartersfamily #oshkoshkids #skiphop
